title: Senior SIGINT Analyst
description: Iraq Oct 2009 – Oct 2010 Used ANCHORY, GOOGLE EARTH, Analyst Notebook, DRT, DISHFIRE, FASCIA, MAINWAY, TAPERLAY, OCTAVE, CONTRAOCTAVE, SIGNAV, BANYAN, CINEPLEX, ASSOCIATION, RENOIR on a daily basis Provided high value intelligence information in support of National/Theatre requirements Developed and analyzed over 30 High Value Targets Authored over 100 time-sensitive tactical reports Responded to over 200 RFIs in support of National/Theatre/Joint Operations Performed analysis and research for target development and reporting of intelligence items Supported mission with key target analysis on adversary capabilities in command’s area of responsibility Responsible for the dissemination of the daily SIGINT summary reports for all Battlefield Commanders Provided time-sensitive geo-location data on targets of interest Supported mission with key target analysis of activity on infrastructure upgrades and technology imports Performed liaison with multiple intra-agency assets Created maps and charts based on collection and analysis of intelligence data Responsible for briefing potential targets and threat groups to multiple echelons in USDS

summary: +Experienced SIGINT Geospatial-Metadata Analyst/Intelligence Analyst/Linguist +Skilled in the use of several Intelligence tools and resources: ANCHORY, AMHS, NUCLEON, TRAFFICTHIEF, ARCMAP, SIGNAV, COASTLINE, DISHFIRE, FASTSCOPE, OCTAVE/CONTRAOCTAVE, PINWALE, UTT, WEBCANDID, MICHIGAN, PLUS, ASSOCIATION, MAINWAY, FASCIA, OCTSKYWARD, INTELINK, METRICS, BANYAN, MARINA + Deployed to use SIGINT to provide Force Protection to American and allied personnel +Acted as primary liaison for NSA during daily teleconferences with other government partners, exchanging ideas and information to maintain complete and up-to-date situational awareness +Translated foreign language materials from Somali and French into English and made targeted briefings to strategic leadership regarding regional security matters +Used a variety of tools and data to provide advanced threat warnings to American civilian, government, and military personnel +Compiled supplemental threat summaries for specific topical meetings of senior leadership, providing them with a fuller global terrorism situational awareness +Prepared topic-specific, detailed presentations for senior leadership using Powerpoint, Word, ZapGrab, ARCMap, and SIGNAV +Routinely wrote articles for CT today, considered a “must-read” by Agency senior leadership and NSA representatives at other organizations. +Collaborated with partners worldwide to enable efficient, real-time support in a 24/7 shift environment +Have worked in both foreign and domestic environments and managed to facilitate smooth exchanges between foreign partners that allowed for maximum efficiency of both parties +Repeatedly called upon to train new employees in a variety of positions +Improved the quality and immediate usefulness of office reporting, directly resulting in an increase of 15% in requests for this product. +Able to filter vast amounts of data and reports to identify key information critical to ongoing projects

company: Overview of Smart Cities and the role of “Safe” in Smart Cities:
description: Some of the other factors that drive Safer City projects are: a strong city economy, level of safety and security threat, availability of internet protocol, susceptibility to natural disasters, improved private and public partnership, and so on. ‘Safer City’ concept is expected to witness significant traction over the next few years as external/internal threat factors are given more importance by governments across the world. The higher the internal/external threat of terrorist attacks, the more probability there is of a city implementing a safer city project. In terms of adoption, the North American market has already seen some rapid progress after the 9/11 attacks. New York City is one of the most “surveilled” cities in the world with video surveillance cameras located at almost every junction, intersection, building, and public area in the city. Other major cities such as Tokyo, Los Angeles, and so on, are on the forefront in adopting safer city projects and related technologies. As critical assets in a city’s infrastructure, security technologies and solutions in future cities will play an important role in promoting better well-being and will support city operators to better cope with security and safety challenges. In the next 5-10 years, Frost & Sullivan expects safer city projects to become integral part of a city’s development schemes proposed by the respective governmen

description: •Release KLIEGHLIGHT and TACREP formatted SIGINT reports for national dissemination and databases. •Review KLIEGHLIGHT and TACREP formatted SIGINT reports and enforce standards of quality IAW RB SOPs and NSA policies. •Review GISTQUEUE gists and enforce standards of quality IAW RB SOPs and NSA policies. •Maintain local archives of all final products, ensuring their orderly storage and adherence to naming conventions IAW the RB SOP. •Identify, diagnose, and troubleshoot communications and system problems as required; report unresolved problems to support personnel. •Supervise the execution of routine RB operations and maintenance. •Initiate and process administrative actions, including awards and evaluations, concerning shift personnel. •Submit gists to appropriate national databases, such as METRICS and GISTQUEUE. •Mark intercepts as appropriate to reflect completed processing. •When required, receive time-sensitive information from LB, and disseminate it as rapidly as possible, in accordance with RB SOPs. •Analyzed and reported raw SIGINT data from air and ground based sources. •Create KLIEGHLIGHT and TACREP formatted SIGINT reports, IAW RB SOPs and NSA policies, using raw-traffic databases to supply approriate amplification. •Provided SIGINT support to Coalition Force/ISAF elements through 24-hour watch operations. •Used remote access to operate the airborne collection platform Pennantrace. company: Overview of Smart Cities and the role of “Safe” in Smart Cities:
description: Some of the other factors that drive Safer City projects are: a strong city economy, level of safety and security threat, availability of internet protocol, susceptibility to natural disasters, improved private and public partnership, and so on. ‘Safer City’ concept is expected to witness significant traction over the next few years as external/internal threat factors are given more importance by governments across the world. The higher the internal/external threat of terrorist attacks, the more probability there is of a city implementing a safer city project. In terms of adoption, the North American market has already seen some rapid progress after the 9/11 attacks. New York City is one of the most “surveilled” cities in the world with video surveillance cameras located at almost every junction, intersection, building, and public area in the city. Other major cities such as Tokyo, Los Angeles, and so on, are on the forefront in adopting safer city projects and related technologies. As critical assets in a city’s infrastructure, security technologies and solutions in future cities will play an important role in promoting better well-being and will support city operators to better cope with security and safety challenges. In the next 5-10 years, Frost & Sullivan expects safer city projects to become integral part of a city’s development schemes proposed by the respective governmen

summary: Mr. Allen, a former U.S. Army Chief Warrant Officer Four, is a Senior Signals Intelligence Analyst and Manager with over 28 years of successful leadership, managerial, product reporting and analytical experience at tactical, joint, combined and multi-national levels in positions of increasing responsibility including two military deployments to Iraq and one civilian deployment to Afghanistan. Mr. Allen is adept at collecting, reviewing, and disseminating intelligence information and providing accurate intelligence products to senior officials and intelligence organizations. summary: Mr. Allen, a former U.S. Army Chief Warrant Officer Four, is a Senior Signals Intelligence Analyst and Manager with over 28 years of successful leadership, managerial, product reporting and analytical experience at tactical, joint, combined and multi-national levels in positions of increasing responsibility including two military deployments to Iraq and one civilian deployment to Afghanistan. Over 25 years active duty service in the U.S. Army and nearly four years as an Army Contract working in senior positions. Experienced in Corps and below intelligence and information operations, including the planning, collection, analysis and distribution of critical information during combat, peace keeping and force protection operations. Mr. Allen also has extensive experience developing architecture with IT solutions and leveraging intelligence disciplines to support military operations/decisions during combat, peace keeping, and force protection missions. Mr. Allen also possesses extensive experience in leading and managing diverse teams, has excellent writing and interpersonal skills, solid analytical and critical thinking skills and strong product reporting/editing skills with experience in Signals Analysis, MASINT, IMINT and Geospatial Metadata Analysis. Mr. Allen is adept at collecting, reviewing, and disseminating intelligence information and providing accurate intelligence products to senior officials and intelligence organizations. Finally, Mr. Allen is a proven analyst, technician, trainer and leader and has always produced exemplary results with 100% mission success.

title: Ground SIGINT Specialist
description: Identifies, researches, and reports target intelligence data in accordance with operational guidance in support of Task Force Operations; provided real-time critical intelligence and threat warning to allied forces saving countless lives Daily utilizes Association, ContraOctave, Dishfire, Homebase, Mainway, Banyan, Cultweave, RTRG, Sortinglead, Taperlay, and Voicemaster to provide near real time analysis and reporting Supports analysis and development of intelligence products; applied traffic analysis techniques to raw data and writes technical, time-sensitive product reports based on national-level intelligence requirements. Coordinates with intelligence analysts throughout the theater of operations to steer reporting efforts and better respond to emerging consumer requirements Trains/mentors junior analysts on various analysis and reporting tools to include of UIS, JCMT, ONEROOF, Center Mass, Gist Queue Monitors UIS to retrieve SRI data in preparation for drafting time-sensitive reports Provides real-time SIGINT support to Multinational Forces and Combat Search and Rescue operations across Afghanistan utilizing RTRG tools and OneRoof, Nucleon, Dishfire and Pinwale database queries Utilizes the following tools to author, compile, retrieve, and send intelligence reports: CPE, Anchory/MAUI , Centermass, Gistgueue, UIS, One Roof, Intelink, and ArcGis; produced over 50 reports per day Provides Collection Management using Joint Collection Management Tools (JCMT) to operational forces Lead analyst on several high profile sensitive reporting efforts Liaises with intelligence community partners on Counter-Insurgency techniques, tactics and procedures, coordinated intelligence sharing with NSA Research Directorate Conducts independent research to write reports to satisfy published customer intelligence requirements Performs social network analysis in Analyst Notebook on Afghanistan threat networks

title: Warrant Officer SIGINT Technician
description: Served as Director and Senior Military Intelligence Analyst; supervised and provided operational analytical support and training for more than 200 Soldiers, 50 DA Civilians and 30 Contractors. Served as the senior advisor to executive level leaders with the responsibility of solving the unit’s Warrant Officer Utilization problems; individually conducted a study and prepared a strategy which allowed senior leaders to effectively utilize Warrant Officers within the organization. Provided input to the staff during the annual review and revision of the units authorization documents (TDAs, MTOEs) based on mission assignments, organizational restructuring and/or higher headquarters directed administrative changes, manpower or equipment surveys, new equipment developments or higher headquarters directed changes. Maintained accountability of sensitive equipment valued at $60 million by conducting monthly physical inventory of non-expendable property and equipment during combat operations. Coordinated and organized the training for more than 1000 Soldiers, DA civilians and contractor on the Equal Opportunity and Equal Employment Opportunity Program. Managed numerous budgets between $85,000.00 and $2.2 million; participated as budget representative to higher echelon in regards to special studies, projects, and meetings. Participated in weekly organizational staff management meetings providing input and representation on contract management, information technology, resource allocation, equipment procurement and incoming and outgoing task/requirements management. Supervised the processing, analysis, reporting, utilization of specialized software and techniques in support of multiple military organizations requirements. Responsible for the planning, directing, coordinating, implementation and evaluation of technical policy and procedures for the sections daily operations.

title: Senior Technical Trainer/Lead
description: Serves as a technical expert in the training and employment of U.S. intelligence systems, providing direction for operations and ensuring compliance with all Department of Defense (DoD) policies, plans, and procedures. Developes and presents complex training programs for customers and in-house employees. Coordinates with program management training, marketing and engineering personnel to identify program needs, obtain technical data and provide schedules for programs of instruction. Test trainees to measure their learning progress and to evaluate effectiveness of training presentations. Conducts training programs on complex topics, and designed and developed training program elements/modules. Provides guidance and direction to less experienced trainers utilizing strong technical and training skills. Reviews or produces technical documentation and recommends measures to improve methods, performance, and the quality of products/services, and suggests changes to increase efficiency/effectiveness in training delivery. Participates with software developers to optimize TGS systems functionality to meet user requirements; provides recommendations for resolution of technical problems where required. Responsible for maintaining and updating the TGS NET Training calendar for all TGS Systems throughout the Army units and National Guard units.

title: New Equipment Training Specialist II
description: • Formulates and executes New Equipment Training (NET) for Program Manager DCGS-A in concert with fielding activities worldwide including hostile fire zones. • Coordinates with program management training, marketing and engineering personnel to identify program needs, obtain technical data and provide schedules for programs of instruction. • Serves as a technical expert in the training and employment of U.S. intelligence systems, providing direction for operations and ensuring compliance with all Department of Defense (DoD) policies, plans, and procedures. • Conducts training programs on complex topics, and designed and developed training program elements/modules. • Possesses the experience to assess training requirements, identify and evaluate training alternatives, develop DCGS-A training materials to include a variety of training techniques: to include traditional classroom, programmed learning, hands-on, simulation, video, audio, and computer aided training. • Reviews or produces technical documentation and recommended measures to improve methods, performance, and the quality of products/services, and suggested changes to increase efficiency/effectiveness in training delivery. • Draws upon practical knowledge to develop Techniques, Tactics & Procedures, mentor soldiers in the practical application and system employment of C4ISR systems and evaluate training developed by the government and other contractors to assess whether or not the training materials meet the Army’s requirements • Responsible for maintaining and updating the Tactical Intelligence Ground Station (TGS) NET Training calendar for all TGS Systems through out the Army units and National Guard units.

title: Ground SIGINT Specialist
description: Identifies, researches, and reports target intelligence data in accordance with operational guidance in support of Task Force Operations; provided real-time critical intelligence and threat warning to allied forces saving countless lives Daily utilizes Association, ContraOctave, Dishfire, Homebase, Mainway, Banyan, Cultweave, RTRG, Sortinglead, Taperlay, and Voicemaster to provide near real time analysis and reporting Supports analysis and development of intelligence products; applied traffic analysis techniques to raw data and writes technical, time-sensitive product reports based on national-level intelligence requirements. Coordinates with intelligence analysts throughout the theater of operations to steer reporting efforts and better respond to emerging consumer requirements Trains/mentors junior analysts on various analysis and reporting tools to include of UIS, JCMT, ONEROOF, Center Mass, Gist Queue Monitors UIS to retrieve SRI data in preparation for drafting time-sensitive reports Provides real-time SIGINT support to Multinational Forces and Combat Search and Rescue operations across Afghanistan utilizing RTRG tools and OneRoof, Nucleon, Dishfire and Pinwale database queries Utilizes the following tools to author, compile, retrieve, and send intelligence reports: CPE, Anchory/MAUI , Centermass, Gistgueue, UIS, One Roof, Intelink, and ArcGis; produced over 50 reports per day Provides Collection Management using Joint Collection Management Tools (JCMT) to operational forces Lead analyst on several high profile sensitive reporting efforts Liaises with intelligence community partners on Counter-Insurgency techniques, tactics and procedures, coordinated intelligence sharing with NSA Research Directorate Conducts independent research to write reports to satisfy published customer intelligence requirements Performs social network analysis in Analyst Notebook on Afghanistan threat networks

title: Warrant Officer SIGINT Technician
description: Served as Director and Senior Military Intelligence Analyst; supervised and provided operational analytical support and training for more than 200 Soldiers, 50 DA Civilians and 30 Contractors. Served as the senior advisor to executive level leaders with the responsibility of solving the unit’s Warrant Officer Utilization problems; individually conducted a study and prepared a strategy which allowed senior leaders to effectively utilize Warrant Officers within the organization. Provided input to the staff during the annual review and revision of the units authorization documents (TDAs, MTOEs) based on mission assignments, organizational restructuring and/or higher headquarters directed administrative changes, manpower or equipment surveys, new equipment developments or higher headquarters directed changes. Maintained accountability of sensitive equipment valued at $60 million by conducting monthly physical inventory of non-expendable property and equipment during combat operations. Coordinated and organized the training for more than 1000 Soldiers, DA civilians and contractor on the Equal Opportunity and Equal Employment Opportunity Program. Managed numerous budgets between $85,000.00 and $2.2 million; participated as budget representative to higher echelon in regards to special studies, projects, and meetings. Participated in weekly organizational staff management meetings providing input and representation on contract management, information technology, resource allocation, equipment procurement and incoming and outgoing task/requirements management. Supervised the processing, analysis, reporting, utilization of specialized software and techniques in support of multiple military organizations requirements. Responsible for the planning, directing, coordinating, implementation and evaluation of technical policy and procedures for the sections daily operations.

title: Intelligence Watch Officer
description: Contracting for the DIA in National Military Command Center (NMCC), National Joint Operations Intelligence Center (NJOIC) section of the Pentagon. Function as a member of a large multi-INT team to provide intelligence support. o Access, review, correlate, and analyze information from multiple intelligence discipline reports daily. Collaborate with Combatant Commands (COCOMs), Services, Intelligence Agencies, and CENTCOM Component Commands and other DoD and interagency organizations. o Produce and disseminate finished intelligence products on global geopolitical problem-sets, including global leadership dynamics, foreign policy, economics, elections, political factions, and opposition groups. Leverage data mining tools/databases such as M3, WISE, WIRe, HOTR, online Economist, Pathfinder, and OSC to provide global geopolitical intelligence products. o Produce and provide intelligence briefings as required. Respond to Command-directed tasks for short and long-term political assessments and products.

title: Sr. Intelligence Analyst
description: Deployed to Iraq in support of project Legacy and Gryphon as a GSE-13 Senior HUMINT Analyst. Embedded with the 2nd Marine Expeditionary Force at Al Asad Air Base and the 3rd Infantry Division at Camp Speicher with the mission of coordinating movement of mission essential personnel and equipment in theater while simultaneously providing program intelligence analysis to the government. o Pooled and processed Human Intelligence from over 30 different locations to produce briefs and reports for key decision makers. o Conducted research and analysis of insurgency, terrorism, conventional operations, information operations, and asymmetric warfare trends and moved HUMINT assets based on the analysis. o Coordinated travel of all program personnel and equipment in the West and North in a timely manner to ensure mission completion. o Created analytical product that assisted in critical decision making and received certificates of exceptional performance while working in a zero supervision environment. o Trained, supervised, and delegated duties to 2 other civilian analysts in theater.

title: Group Product Manager
description: Sydney, Australia; August 2008 – present • Head of APAC Monetization: Managed team of 10 Product Managers and efforts of over one hundred engineers. Drove product innovation across Search, Display, and Billing & Payments, representing several billion dollars of revenue. • Head of Australia/New Zealand Products: Managed five Product Managers and efforts of over fifty engineers to develop global products across Geo, App Engine, Apps, and Real Estate. Responsible for ensuring the success of all Google products in Australia/New Zealand, assisting with Government Relations, and co-managing office of over 300 employees. Mountain View, CA; October 2004 – July 2008 • Head of Display Platforms: Managed five product managers and efforts of 120 engineers across Advertiser and Publisher Display Ad Serving Platforms. Launched Google Ad Manager which is now the world’s second most popular ad server. • DoubleClick Acquisition Lead: Co-led the acquisition and integration efforts of the $3.2BB purchase. Participated in Board of Director’s discussion and held monthly meetings with Google CEO and Founders. • AdWords API and 3rd Party Developer Program: Launched AdWords API and developed third party developer ecosystem. Much of Google’s revenue flows through this channel. • Click to Call: Launched failed attempt at generating phone leads for small businesses. Developed new pricing system (per call), Ad Format, Ad Ranking system, and user calling technology. • Launched Ad Review Center and Ads Diagnostic Tool, Ads Privacy Council Member, and initial co-lead of AdWords Front-End Rewrite. Achievements • Four-time OC Award winner (annual company-wide award for five to ten teams that have had an extraordinary impact on the company; four awards is amongst the most across all employees).

summary: Rishi is the product lead for Chromecast. His favorite things to watch are anything to do with sports and shows that involve Larry David. Chandra has been fortunate to be involved in several major launches at Google. He joined Google in 2006 to launch Google Apps, Google's online suite of communication and collaboration tools for businesses and schools. In 2010, Chandra launched Google TV, a new TV platform based on Android that is in embedded in televisions and set-top boxes. In 2013, Chandra launched Chromecast, a new device that allows people to use their phone, tablet or laptop to easily stream content from the cloud to their televisions. Prior to joining Google, Rishi worked as a consultant at strategy consulting firm Bain & Company. Rishi holds degrees in computer science and business administration from the University of California, Berkeley, as well as an MBA from Stanford University.

title: Senior Cyber SME/ All-source-SIGINT Analyst
description: - Liaised with partners to identify gaps in IO system capabilities, map existing/planned CNO capabilities against COCOM requirements, and align mission planning to the Integrated Joint Special Technical Operations review and approval process. - Directed the activities of personnel conducting analysis, planning, development, and cyber operational initiatives - Uses various tools to facilitate partner CNO tasking and QC partner’s CNO tasking requests. - Involved with NSA/TAO Cyber mission planning, coordination, and deconfliction process. - Provided SIGINT/CYBER information and threat warning, during real time global operations for multiple U.S. and partner organizations using support tools and real-time source databases. - Conducted operations for Fleet combatants and shore commands; supporting EUCOM, AFRICOM, CYBERCOM, and NSA/CSS. - Project manager for multiple missions in hostile locations, spanning equipment installs, trouble shooting, personnel training, budget management, diplomatic relations, collection and logistics - Collection manager in support of aerial operation to include combat operations and provided tasking for theater level commanders. Identified collection priorities daily, corrected data flow problems and provided weekly statistics on accuracy of data. - Primary cyber intelligence analyst for all operations, eliminating incorrect collection and providing a “First Look” on all collection to turn around actionable intelligence within 24 hours. - Liaison with foreign partner providing CNO/SIGINT training, tasking, budgeting, and overall diplomatic relations. - Assistant Cryptologic Resource Manager; planned, managed and tasked collection and intelligence assets in accordance with U.S. Navy and NSA/CSS priorities. QC’d all reports from U.S. Naval Vessels in the EUCOM/AFRICOM AOR. - Managed, administered, and maintained all Special Access Program personnel, equipment, and accesses without a single discrepancy for four years.

title: CEO
description: Mobile Health One is developing a cloud-based, HIPAA-secure mobile communication platform - MDChat™. MDChat™ directly connects healthcare providers with each other, with their patients, and with the information they need when they need it. MHO’s solution improves patient outcomes by accelerating communication and access to information while reducing errors and costs. MDChat™ enables secure, seamless communication and collaboration between healthcare providers, administrative personnel and patients. The system incorporates secure messaging, auto-patient tracking/physician notification, telehealth, remote monitoring of patient devices and wearables, and secure sharing of images and documents, 24/7 – all on the same mobile dashboard. MDChat On Call™ enables direct, 24/7 communication between patients and their doctor, or their doctor’s on-call medical staff, and administrative personnel (like the billing department) eliminating the need for a live operator. The system incorporates a web/mobile on-call scheduling system, a secure “chat” widget for the client web site and voice recognition/response to support direct communication between providers, patients, on-call staff, and administrative departments. MDChat On Call™ reduces live operator costs by up to 70% and ensures HIPAA compliance. MDView™ is a cloud-based radiology image viewing and sharing system for healthcare providers and patients. Users can access their own library of image studies and share them with any healthcare provider as needed. MDView™ eliminates the need to put image studies on discs, reducing costs by more than 80%. MHO is the first health IT company to perform real time identity verification in the cloud enabling system users to communicate on-demand with anyone, anywhere – regardless of where they work or what device(s) they carry. To learn more, visit www.MDChat.com and www.MDView.com.

title: Network Administrator and Information Technology Specialist
description: Serves as an Information Technology NCO/Signal Support Systems NCO in a Military Intelligence Battalion; supervises, installs, operates and performs unit level maintenance on multi-functional/multi-user information processing systems, peripheral equipment, and associated devices in both tactical and garrison configurations; requisitions, receives, stores, issues, and accounts for COMSEC equipment, and associated keying material; enforces Army network security and information assurance policies. As Signal Support Systems NCO supervises and integrates the installation, operation and maintenance of signal support systems, to include radio, wire, cable and battlefield automated systems; plans, and provides training and support for the Division’s local area networks, wide area networks and routers which service over 10,000 users. Responsible for the morale, welfare, and professional development of one junior NCO, and nine Soldiers; responsible for automation equipment worth in excess of $250,000. Responsible for establishing all lines of communications during annual training events to include networking, setting up TOCs, installation and training of all HARRIS and SINCGAR radios. Daily Duties: ● Installed, configured, and administered SUN Solaris 9.x-10.x network for 200+ users. ● Managed and configured boot image files, created and configured VLANS, and programmed Access Control Lists on CISCO routers and switches. ● Installed, configured, and managed Active Directory infrastructure and messaging services.

title: SIGINT Analyst
company: US Army and US Army Reserves
description: Performed advanced analysis on intercepted communications and non-communications signals information; analyzes technical documents and reports; supervises correlation and fusion of SIGINT operations; coordinates the SIGINT ISR synchronization process to determine mission objectives, priorities and tasks based on mission requirements; reviews intelligence reports; writes, edits, evaluates and publishes SIGINT reports; provides direction to subordinate Analysts; assists Platoon Sergeant with accountability and mission management as Shift Supervisor and Squad Leader for three Soldiers. As the Reporting NCOIC for USF-I and USD-S I was responsible for converting all TS/SCI reports into SECRET level reports that were distributed to all land owners throughout Iraq. Performed duties outside of awarded MOS; lauded for his utilization of six analytical and technical databases to answer Requests for Information and trained a shift of 7 analysts in the use of Boolean logic; directly resulted in the ability of all 7 analysts to utilize two new intelligence databases. I utilized knowledge of Boolean logic and computer skills to become subject matter expert of UIS database providing specific queries and tools for linguists to maximize efficiency. Responsible for IEW equipment worth in excess of $750,000. Created, disseminated and briefed daily intelligence, operational, enemy activity and equipment status reports to commanders in support or Operation New Dawn.

title: SIGINT Analyst and Linguist
description: ● Deployed directly supporting combat operations overseas with the 319th Battle Field Surveillance Brigade ● Supervised and managed a team sized tactical signal intelligence collection and analysis team ● Night shift Non Commissioned Officer in Charge (NCOIC) analyst in a team size signal intelligence analysis and collection element in support of missions conducted by Brigade Combat teams ● Developed time sensitive geospatial metadata analysis and geo location target packages for Brigade Combat teams with a specific concentration on the local area of responsibility ● Aided in the processing intelligence support requests (SSR’s) for 3/1 CAV and 25th ID signals intelligence mission; supported successful operations against multiple high value targets ● Assisted in the training of multiple soldiers on how to effectively conduct time sensitive geospatial spatial metadata analysis in both GSM and HPCP in support of future mission operations in Afghanistan and Iraq ● Cross-trained in Human Intelligence analysis and tactics, to include Cellular exploitation, Document exploitation, Site exploitation and Media exploitation; while serving as a member of a MFT ● Participated in classroom training and field training on various platforms and DRT to include signal analysis, triangulation, and direction finding exercises ● Operates collection systems to provide timely, accurate information to aid in time-sensitive operations against high value targets ● Collaborates with remote intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance (ISR) professionals in order to provide near real-time support for operations ● Analyzes, collects and optimizes data configurations to refine geo-location solutions ● Prepares and disseminates technical reports and geo-locations to war-fighters ● Performed duties of Mission Manager while leadership was sent to other locations or while on leave. ● Tracked and maintained accountability of over 40 HUMINT, SIGINT and Counter-Intelligence teams and their assets.

title: Program Manager, SOSi Mission Support–Iraq, Mission Solutions Group
description: • Recruited and hired as the Program Manager and Subject Matter Expert to lead the SOSi Mission Support - Iraq (SMS-I) team into a market where corporately SOS International LLC. had not previously ventured • Annual revenue in excess of $175M • Full P&L responsibility • Leadership as the senior SMS-I in-country representative to Foreign Military Sales customers (FMS), accountable for rendering outstanding Base Life Support services, including Facilities Operations and Maintenance, Construction, Emergency Services, Medical, Security (static and mobile), Information Technology, Procurement, Supply Chain and Finance • Successful transition of Base Life Support mission at two sites on schedule and below budget from the existing United States Government contractor to a solely commercial service (this is the first time this has ever been accomplished) • Solely responsible for the creation of all required operating budgets, staffing BOE’s, policies, procedures and processes necessary for the successful transition and startup of a program • Championed and successfully implemented a Continuous Improvement Plan that reduced operating costs by an astounding 38% over first year • Facilitation of all in-country activities while serving as liaison with clients (General Dynamics Land Systems, Bell Helicopter, Lockheed Martin, Raytheon, Textron, Boeing, Northrup Grumman and Fluor), United States Embassy, Government of Iraq, Prime Minister’s Office, Ministry of Defense, Iraqi Army & Aviation Senior Commands and SMS-I Joint Venture ❖ SMS-I was the only US organization outside of the US Embassy that maintained its presence in Iraq while ISIS was advancing towards Baghdad during the summer of 2014. SMS-I continued to perform daily operations without missing a single mission during this timeframe.

title: Deputy Regional Director/ LOGCAP IV
description: • Provided the full range of life support and facilities management services on a contract valued at over $6.2B. • Leadership and direction over 3 HUBs, including 17 forward operating bases (FOBs) in support of more than 30,000 US and International Security Assistance Force (ISAF) military personnel. • Responsible for all activities within the region to include contractual compliance in accordance with the Performance Work Statement (PWS) and project completion of “New Work” and construction projects • Exceptional support to senior management by providing advice as well as administrative and operational expertise • Full accountability in overseeing all personnel, property, and equipment allocated to the region while directing a group of more than 6,000 DynCorp International (DI) and subcontracted employees • Active collaboration with program staff to ascertain on-time and systematic execution of contractual requirements • Prepared and briefed quarterly and bi-monthly Performance Evaluation Boards to government officials. Consistently met and or exceeded performance standards • Planned, coordinated, resourced, and tracked successful descope operations at ten sites • Frequent selection by the program management to conduct key investigations and process improvement to theater issues regarding the program ★ Recipient of the DI Star Award for demonstrating exceptional work performance

title: Site Manager, LOGCAP IV
description: • Effectively administered DOD contract valued in excess of $110M • Performed the duties equivalent to a City Manager, responsible for the coordination and synchronization of Power Generation; Facilities Operations and Maintenance; Construction, Food Service Operations; Laundry Operations; Morale Welfare and Recreation; Airfield/ Runway/ Tower Operations, Sewage and Waste Management; Bulk and Retail Fuel; Transportation Maintenance; Shuttle Bus Operations; Fire Fighting and Emergency Services; Water Production and Distribution; and other services in support of a 12,000 person Forward Operating Base • Leadership and guidance to more than 1,750 DI and subcontract personnel aboard Camp Dwyer, Afghanistan in carrying out base life support services for the US Military • Creation of various processes and facilitation of staff training to effectively execute timely delivery of contract deliverables (CDRLs) and reports • Production of new performance work statement (PWS) functions funding, which included requirement development • Cultivation of strong working relationships with onsite Administrative Contracting Officer (ACO), quality assurance representative (QAR), LOGCAP support officer (LSO), mayor cell, and other organizations supported by LOGCAP • Adept direction to the entire phases of contractual projects, which included design, estimations, resource allocation, staffing, and management while ensuring the completion within the government-approved delivery timeline • Accomplishment of Camp Dwyer services transition from incumbent ahead of United States Government (USG) timeline • Establishment of site startup operations of FOB's Deleram and Payne, which included camp construction

summary: My career history demonstrates a highly competent leader and logistics program manager that consistently achieves outlined goals and objectives. With 16+ years of experience in land, sea, and air transportation management in international locations, I have worked in high-risk, tumultuous, and culturally diverse Middle Eastern countries. Throughout my career I have exhibited a sophisticated approach to operational oversight, transportation execution, and logistics management. Adept at vendor management, resource allocation, and expediting results, I consistently deliver timely and accurate results that exceed customer and client expectations. I earned the reputation as a qualified manager who leads by example, is a motivational leader, and effective trainer; I have directed organizations with hundreds of personnel. With a commitment to excellence, I establish high standards and expectations of my staff to deliver safety, quality, efficiency, productivity, cost containment, and compliance. I have successfully managed site logistics and compliance for hazardous material handling and hazardous waste sites, including the oversight of safety and security alerts to ensure employee compliance of established procedures. I began my career with the United States Army, where I earned increasing levels of responsibility by demonstrating my hard work and dedication to motivating teams and driving results. I applied my 13+ years’ experience executing logistics and operations in the military into the corporate arena supporting government contracts in war-torn locations. I demonstrate extreme cultural awareness and sensitivity, which results in effective rapport building and desired results. It is my goal to utilize my leadership, management, logistics, operations, and international business expertise in a new and challenging position where I can add immediate value to the sustained growth and success of your organization. Additionally, I hold an active secret clearance.Specialties:Logistics, Management, IT Technician, MS Office Suite, Desktop Repair, Warehousing, Storage, Parts Issue, Transportation

title: Professional Recruiter

summary: Apex Systems, an On Assignment company (NYSE: ASGN), provides organizations with scalable IT staffing solutions to address critical gaps in their current workforce and augment workforce management strategies. We specialize in providing IT professionals for contract, contract-to-hire, direct placement, and managed solutions to clients in Fortune 500, mid-market, and emerging companies. Our specialized technology and industry practice groups help us match the most talented and qualified technical professionals to great companies across the country. Apex and parent company On Assignment combine to be the 2nd largest IT staffing and services firm in the U.S. Apex was named to Inavero’s Best of Staffing™ Client lists in 2012 and 2013. At Apex, we take pride in offering best-in-class customer service and unrivaled market and industry knowledge to match our clients’ needs with highly-qualified IT professionals. Our goal is to act as a business partner to our clients and help them build and maintain successful IT leadership and support departments. We take time to understand our client’s vision, challenges and goals; thus, helping them to tailor an appropriate staffing model to achieve business targets. Visit www.apexsystemsinc.com to learn more about Apex and view our current job openings.

summary: Apex Systems, an On Assignment company (NYSE: ASGN), provides organizations with scalable IT staffing solutions to address critical gaps in their current workforce and augment workforce management strategies. We specialize in providing IT professionals for contract, contract-to-hire, direct placement, and managed solutions to clients in Fortune 500, mid-market, and emerging companies. Our specialized technology and industry practice groups help us match the most talented and qualified technical professionals to great companies across the country. Apex and parent company On Assignment combine to be the 2nd largest IT staffing and services firm in the U.S. Apex was named to Inavero’s Best of Staffing™ Client lists in 2012 and 2013. At Apex, we take pride in offering best-in-class customer service and unrivaled market and industry knowledge to match our clients’ needs with highly-qualified IT professionals. Our goal is to act as a business partner to our clients and help them build and maintain successful IT leadership and support departments. We take time to understand our client’s vision, challenges and goals; thus, helping them to tailor an appropriate staffing model to achieve business targets. Visit www.apexsystemsinc.com to learn more about Apex and view our current job openings.

title: Program Manager
description: As Senior Program Manager, I have experience across a wide range of contract types including Firm-Fixed Price (FFP), Time and Material (T&M), Cost-Plus Award Fee (CPAF) and Fixed Fee service contracts in the Intelligence Community (IC). I have successfully managed subcontractors and Performance-Based prime contracts in the role of Business and Program Manager for major acquisitions and oversaw teams conducting requirements generation, and performed team (as many as 50 sub on one contract) evaluations. I have managed programs funding plans to monitor and identify potential cost and schedule risks, and produced Basis of Estimates (BOE) for future program initiatives. I readily demonstrate leadership skills through versatility, with the ability to effectively engage, communicate, and interact with various support staff ranging from junior technical professionals to senior level management. As Program Manager, I took the program from the Capture phase (win), leading the Transition, to Execution on contracts ranging from +$200M to +$1B!

summary: Strengths: Goal Oriented; Persistent; Execute Plans; Anticipate Obstacles; Develop Teams, Value Driven, Dedicated, Determined, Enthusiastic I take great pride and satisfaction in achieving goals, using strategic analysis in-line with our customers and company stakeholder’s needs. These achievements are obtained by building and developing teams that work together to overcome challenges—we focus on our strengths and look for ways to adjust our processes, as well as anticipate obstacles for seamless execution. Excel in the following: I continuously look for ways to advance a process or overcome a barrier. I use knowledge and experience in conducting process assessment/evaluation, analysis of business workflows and task organization. I remain abreast of best practices to optimize business processes to align with industry best practices that meet customer needs. I apply intelligence expertise and technical writing skills in the development, submission and presentation of white papers and program briefs (including technical, managerial and financial data) for system and component capability, acquisition status, and proof-concept systems).

title: Project and Program Manager
description: As Project and Program Manager, I have experience across a wide range of contract types including Firm-Fixed Price (FFP), Time and Material (T&M), Cost-Plus Award Fee (CPAF) and Fixed Fee service contracts in the Intelligence Community (IC). I have successfully managed subcontractors and Performance-Based prime contracts in the role of Business and Program Manager for major acquisitions and oversaw teams conducting requirements generation, and performed team (as many as 50 sub on one contract) evaluations. I have managed programs funding plans to monitor and identify potential cost and schedule risks, and produced Basis of Estimates (BOE) for future program initiatives. I readily demonstrate leadership skills through versatility, with the ability to effectively engage, communicate, and interact with various support staff ranging from junior technical professionals to senior level management. As Program Manager, I took the program from the Capture phase (win), leading the Transition, to Execution on contracts ranging from +$60M-$120M

title: Sr. Internal Control Auditor
description: • Identify, and report deficiencies in internal applications, and coordinate with internal development teams to implement security enhancements in application and application permissions. • Manage assignment and documentation of role-based access permissions in internal application. • Provide guidance to management and development on the planning, coordination, and implementation of security controls in absence of other documentation or guidance. • Provide guidance to third party auditors on state of information system security controls. • Provide continual information security training to an employee base of employees of both technical and non-technical disciplines • Provide on-boarding Compliance training to Sales on standards and internal compliance efforts and responsibilities • Assist Customers and Sales Engineers in identification and implementation of internal and customer control responsibilities • Collect documentation and assist third-party auditors during system security assessments to assess state of security controls of complex internal information systems. • Design, document, implement, and carry out audit procedures for physical and logical system access. • Design and document Information Security policy and procedure. • Facilitation of change to existing processes to increase overall information system security posture. • Communication and Coordination with Senior-level (VP and C-Level) management for control implementation. • Document and delegate information system vulnerability remediation efforts. • Track and report emerging trends in information security.

description: Key Responsibilities: * Work with auditors and senior IT Management during various security assessments to ascertain the status of implemented security controls in accordance with NIST 800-53 security controls, and AICPA trust services criteria. *Draft and maintenance of internal policies and procedures covering the SoftLayer platform, infrastructure, and proprietary automated provisioning system. *Perform quarterly audits to provide assurance on the appropriateness of both logical and physical access on internal applications, corporate network, and datacenter. *Document operational security controls within applicable policies and procedures. *Conduct Risk Assessments on mission-critical internal systems. *Implementation and maintenance of new permissions tree, creating baseline permission sets for over 200 user groups, spanning 700+ employees, in order to better enforce separation of duties and least privilege through the use of nondiscretionary access control models.

description: MOSAIC Technologies Group Inc. (MOSAIC) provides top of the line Mission Support services to the Department of Defense and other Intelligence Agencies across the Intelligence Community. MOSAIC fully understands the unique capability Mission Support provides to our customers, and we deploy subject matter experts to handle all tasks and projects with precision, timeliness and accuracy. Our analysts and reporters work with many Department of Defense and Intelligence Community customers, have strong foundations, and demonstrated aptitude in multi-disciplined intelligence and language analysis within the following areas: regional threat analysis, order of battle analysis, foreign military capabilities, infra-structure analysis, foreign leadership biographies, indications and warning or targeting. Our analysts stand prepared and ready to research, draft, edit, review, interpret, evaluate, and integrate intelligence information to assess regional developments, trends and threat implications.

summary: Executive Summary: IEEE 2015 Outstanding Engineer of Region 6 Central Area (Central California, Nevada, Hawaii). Coordinate intellectual property system, strategy, due diligence for leading CMOS image sensor manufacturer. High-tech patent analysis, assertion case prep, claim vs product attribute charts, prior art searches, reverse engineering, market analysis, IP valuation, inventor interviews, negotiation support, multi-project support. Recent patent projects: IC I/O drivers, PC User Interface, MEMS, IC Fab processes, CDMA/GSM wireless, telecomm. M&A pre-investment due diligence of IP. Commercialization of University research. IC device physics, fabrication processes Non-Volatile memory, MRAM, Flash. Cu interconnects, Low K dielectrics, CMP Photolithography, layer deposition, etching. Audit IC & MEMS fabrication facilities, processes, & reliability issue prevention. Assessment of technology capability, risks. NSF Grant Peer reviewer – SBIR semi mfg. Hold 5 granted and 9 pending US patents. Delphion, Patent Magic, & USPTO tools. Professional Summary: Over 43 years experience in the semiconductor Industry with broad exposure to electronics. 9+ years experience in patent analysis, assertion support, valuation, related Reverse Engineering. Expert Program Manager - introduced cross functional team process in semiconductors. Directed development of fabrication processes for semiconductor devices and ICs Assessed IC fabrication technology maturity at factories in Japan, Taiwan, Europe, Singapore, Malaysia & the US, for capability & readiness for high volume manufacture. Specialties: High-tech patent analysis, drafting,assertion case prep, claim vs product attribute charts, prior art searches, reverse engineering, market analysis, IP valuation, inventor interviews, negotiation support, multi-project support. Manage Advanced CMOS and BiCMOS IC fabrication process development.

title: Geospatial Analyst/Sensor Planner
description: • Build, assess, and implement multiple U-2 navigational tracks and sensor plans, as well as generate and distribute Mission Control notes to collect enemy targets in support of combatant commanders for multiple military operations • Direct and re-task U-2 pilot and control airborne imagery and signals intelligence sensors in coordination with the Mission Operations Commander (MOC), Imagery Mission Supervisor (IMS), and Ground Mission Supervisor (GMS) using an array of applications to ensure connectivity, interoperability and security of aircraft and crew in hostile territory. • Serve as an effective Instructor Rated Operator (IRO) responsible for facilitating training of employees. • Conduct comparative coverage analysis, interpret and evaluate Senior Year Electro-Optical Reconnaissance System 2 (SYERS-2), Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR), Electro-Optical (EO), Thermal Infrared (IR), Multi-Spectral, Measurement and Signatures Intelligence (MASINT), Advanced Geospatial Intelligence (AGI), and Full Motion Video (FMV) softcopy imagery. • Interpret, compare, mensurate, classify, and evaluate imagery to determine the number, type, dimension, location, function, and significance of civilian and military activity, objects and equipment, and physical and cultural ground features to satisfy Essential Elements of Information (EEI). • Create detailed threat analysis of enemy units' movement and force disposition to produce actionable, near-real-time combat intelligence to theater combatant commanders and warfighting forces, bolstering force protection. • Prepare time sensitive reports, Initial and Second Phase Interpretation Reports (IPIR), briefings, and tailored imagery products on installations worldwide utilizing imagery interpretation keys and reference publications in support of wartime operations for customers across five Combatant Commands.
